# Scaffold Feature

Use this skill for new feature delivery that spans documentation and code.

## Inputs

- Feature name
- Short description or desired user outcome
- Any explicit platform or scope constraints

## Workflow

1. Ask only for missing inputs needed to name or scope the feature.
2. Read `docs/advisory-board.md` and run the board review first.
3. Create or update `docs/features/{feature-name}.md` from `docs/features/_template.md`.
4. Create or update `backend/docs/entities/*.md` for every new or changed backend entity.
5. Update `shared/api-contracts/openapi.yml` following `docs/api/conventions.md`.
6. Run `task generate-clients`.
7. Implement the affected platform slices:
{% if "backend" in platforms %}- `backend/`
{% endif %}{% if "web-user-app" in platforms %}- `web-user-app/`
{% endif %}{% if "web-admin-portal" in platforms %}- `web-admin-portal/`
{% endif %}{% if "mobile-android" in platforms %}- `mobile-android/`
{% endif %}{% if "mobile-ios" in platforms %}- `mobile-ios/`
{% endif %}
8. Update the feature doc checklist and status with what was completed, deferred, or blocked.

## Guardrails

- Create or update documentation before code.
- Follow the platform-specific `AGENTS.md` files when working inside a platform.
- Reuse generated clients instead of inventing ad-hoc request models.
- Keep partial implementations explicit in the feature doc.
